Pawan Passi was the head of equity syndicate at Morgan Stanley. Big banking=
 clients =E2=80=94=C2=A0corporations, private equity firms =E2=80=94=C2=A0w=
ould sometimes come to Morgan Stanley for block trades, saying =E2=80=9Cwe=
=E2=80=99re going to sell a big block of stock in Company X after the close=
 today and we will want a bid from you, but don=E2=80=99t tell anyone, this=
 is highly confidential.=E2=80=9D Passi would then call some of his favorit=
e hedge fund customers and say =E2=80=9Chey, there=E2=80=99s a big block of=
 Company X coming after the close today, get ready.=E2=80=9D The hedge fund=
s would then short the stock, knowing that they would be able to buy at a d=
iscount in the block trade and make a quick profit. Morgan Stanley would be=
 better positioned to win the block trade, because it had already lined up =
buyers (the hedge funds). Good for Morgan Stanley, good for Passi, good for=
 the hedge funds.
Bad for the client =E2=80=94=C2=A0the seller of the block =E2=80=94=C2=A0wh=
o expected=C2=A0Morgan Stanley to keep the deal confidential and who probab=
ly got a lower price on the trade.
  [1]
=C2=A0Eventually this was discovered, Passi was fired, Morgan Stanley paid =
a big fine, Passi paid a smaller fine and was banned from the securities in=
dustry for a year, and presumably the Morgan Stanley clients whose block tr=
ades were leaked =E2=80=94=C2=A0firms like Blackstone, Oaktree and Cinven=
=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0were mad about it, though when Bloomberg News asked th=
em they declined to comment.
  [2]

On the other hand, presumably the hedge fund customers were pleased with th=
e customer service they got from Passi, and sad to see it end. They were ne=
ver accused of wrongdoing, and they got to keep their profits. =E2=80=9CI k=
now who my daddy is,=E2=80=9D one of them told Passi. And now Bloomberg=E2=
=80=99s=C2=A0Sridhar Natarajan, Ava Benny-Morrison, and Katherine Burton re=
port:

A former Morgan Stanley banker who was punished in the block-trading probe =
that rattled Wall Street joined one of the firms that was the recipient of =
confidential information he leaked.
Pawan Passi was hired by Frank Fu=E2=80=99s CaaS Capital Management, accord=
ing to people familiar with the matter. CaaS made its name partnering with =
banks as they sought buyers for block trades, becoming one of the biggest U=
S funds dedicated to buying big chunks of stocks.=C2=A0

I love it.
  [3]
=C2=A0Really the least they could do! Presumably Passi=E2=80=99s knowledge =
of the block trade market will be helpful to a block trade specialist. But =
also developing a reputation for helping out down-on-their-luck equity synd=
icate bankers should be helpful to a block trade specialist. If your busine=
ss is partnering with banks for block trades, being nice to the bankers mig=
ht encourage more banks to partner with you.
Honestly though this story would be funnier if Passi turned up, not at CaaS=
 or one of the other hedge funds he helped, but at Blackstone or Oaktree or=
 one of the other private equity firms he=C2=A0harmed. Really Blackstone sh=
ould hire him as its head of block trades. On the one hand, probably bad in=
centives. On the other hand, he knows all the tricks.=C2=A0

