=C2=A0Thorp</a> about how he has perhaps discovered the secret to eternal l=
ife but is being relatively chill and low-key about it:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Less well known is that Thorp has devoted his =
talents as much to health and longevity as to beating casinos and markets. =
At 91 he=E2=80=99s remarkably healthy and vigorous. Although he=E2=80=99s n=
o longer running marathons or doing serious weight training, Thorp jogs and=
 works out at the gym regularly. He weighs 155=E2=80=942 pounds above his w=
eight at age 17=E2=80=94and can do two chin-ups and 15 pushups. He analyzes=
 scientific literature and manages his regimen carefully. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Bloomberg Businessweek: We=E2=80=99ve =
heard you quoted as saying you =E2=80=9Cbeat the dealer, beat the market an=
d are going to beat the man upstairs.=E2=80=9D Is that right?</strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think I said something like that. Well, mayb=
e I=E2=80=99d modify it to =E2=80=9Cpush the man upstairs back as far as I =
can.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He gets into details on his approach, which in=
volves diet, exercise, some supplements, and apparently not yet transfusion=
s of young people=E2=80=99s blood because =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m not under pr=
essure to stretch for these things that might work because I=E2=80=99m doin=
g OK right now,=E2=80=9D but=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cif I were in bad shape, I might =
need to take some risk to get into less bad shape.=E2=80=9D He also mention=
s that he missed out on investing in Renaissance Technologies in the 1980s,=
 because he =E2=80=9Clearned that [Jim Simons] smoked in meetings=E2=80=9D =
and =E2=80=9Cjust didn=E2=80=99t want the exposure.=E2=80=9D (To smoke, pre=
sumably, not to Renaissance=E2=80=99s strategy.) You can construct a rough =
hierarchy of Thorp=E2=80=99s priorities in which trading profits come ahead=
 of academic glory, but longevity comes ahead of trading profits. Seems lik=
e a reasonable hierarchy.</p>
